org.apache.beam.sdk.values

Class BeamRecord

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.apache.beam.sdk.values.BeamRecord
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    @Experimental
public class BeamRecord
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable
    BeamRecord is an immutable tuple-like type to represent one element in a PCollection. The fields are described with a BeamRecordType.

    By default, BeamRecordType only contains the name for each field. It can be extended to support more sophisticated validation by overwriting BeamRecordType.validateValueType(int, Object).

    A Coder BeamRecordCoder is provided, which wraps the Coder for each data field.

    See Also:
